text.tspan: OpenCV Feature Detection
The first thing we worked on was determining an opencv tool to help us identify the anchor ear
in the comparison images. We wanted a key feature detector that would be able to make key
points across both the anchor image and comparison image accurately and consistently. We
experimented with SURF, ORB, and SIFT, and eventually decided on SIFT because even
though it wasn’t the fastest, it produced key points that we felt would work better with our
closeup ear anchor image. Combining SIFT with the flann key point matcher algorithm gave us
great matches that worked on images with no difference. For example, the image below is
matching the anchor image with a zoomed out anchor image.
